### Course Management API Tests

### 1. Create a new course
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "courseCode": "CS101",
  "title": "Introduction to Computer Science",
  "description": "A comprehensive introduction to computer science fundamentals",
  "credits": 3,
  "lecturerId": 1,
  "startDate": "2024-01-15",
  "endDate": "2024-05-15",
  "capacity": 30,
  "courseMetadata": "{\"prerequisites\": [], \"department\": \"Computer Science\"}"
}

### 2. Create another course
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "courseCode": "MATH201",
  "title": "Calculus I",
  "description": "Introduction to differential and integral calculus",
  "credits": 4,
  "startDate": "2024-01-15",
  "endDate": "2024-05-15",
  "capacity": 25,
  "courseMetadata": "{\"prerequisites\": [\"MATH101\"], \"department\": \"Mathematics\"}"
}

### 3. Get all courses (paginated)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses?page=0&size=10&sort=title,asc

### 4. Get course by ID
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/1

### 5. Get course by code
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/code/CS101

### 6. Search courses by title
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/search?title=Computer&page=0&size=10

### 7. Get courses by lecturer
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/lecturer/1?page=0&size=10

### 8. Get upcoming courses
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/upcoming?page=0&size=10

### 9. Get courses by date range
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/date-range?startDate=2024-01-01&endDate=2024-12-31&page=0&size=10

### 10. Get courses by credits
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/credits/3?page=0&size=10

### 11. Get courses by credits range
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/credits-range?minCredits=2&maxCredits=4&page=0&size=10

### 12. Get courses by minimum capacity
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/capacity/20?page=0&size=10

### 13. Update course
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/1
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Advanced Introduction to Computer Science",
  "description": "An advanced comprehensive introduction to computer science fundamentals",
  "credits": 4,
  "capacity": 35
}

### 14. Update course with new lecturer
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/2
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "lecturerId": 2,
  "courseMetadata": "{\"prerequisites\": [\"MATH101\"], \"department\": \"Mathematics\", \"updated\": true}"
}

### 15. Delete course
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/2

### 16. Try to create course with duplicate code (should fail)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "courseCode": "CS101",
  "title": "Duplicate Course",
  "description": "This should fail",
  "credits": 2
}

### 17. Try to get non-existent course (should fail)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/999

### 18. Try to update non-existent course (should fail)
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/999
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "This should fail"
}

### 19. Try to delete non-existent course (should fail)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/v1/courses/999

